<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <!-- Bootstrap CSS via CDN -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/axios/dist/axios.min.js"></script><!-- Import Axios here, this will load it gloabally, so that you can use it inside of the script.js file, if you dont load axios here you wont be able to use it inside of an external js script file -->
</head>
<body>
    <div class="main">
     <div class="heading-container">
        <h1>The cocktail app</h1>
     </div>   
    <div class="main-container">
            <!--Card-->
            <div class="card">
            <img src="<%=imageUrl%>" alt="Dynamically loaded image">  <!--Dynamically pass image from backend to front end to mathch the drink, fi you dont you will have to reload the page, there was an error that occured you neeed to copy the relative path instead of the absolute path, you dont neeed to start from the top of the folder, I believe this is due to ejs and the relationship with public so in this case you would start the path from the images folder then to the image.jpg-->
                <div class="container">
                    <h4>Name of Coctail: 
                        <%if(locals.name_of_drink){%>
                            <%=name_of_drink%>
                        <%}%>
                        </h4>
                    <p>
                        <h5>Instructions:</h5>
                        <%if(locals.instructions){%>
                            <%=instructions%>
                        <%}%>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="button-container">
           <!-- <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" id="fetchData">Get cocktail</button>  -->
            <form action="/get-data" method="get"><!-- This button is connected to the get-data endpoint, action is set to /get-data, it has a get method -->
                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Get New Cocktail</button> 
            </form>
        </div>
        
    </div>
    <!--Scripts-->
    <!-- <script src="/script.js"></script> -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
   <!-- <script src="script.js" type="module"></script> --> <!--This is the script.js file that should be linked at the bottom of the file-->
</body>
</html>